text: Palaquium luzoniense, also called red nato, is a species of plant in the family Sapotaceae. It is endemic to the Philippines. It is threatened by habitat loss. ==References== luzoniense Category:Flora of the Philippines Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot Category:Plants described in 1880 Category:Taxa named by Celestino Fernández-Villar
